<paragraph blockId="13.[835,1436,503,963]" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis box="[864,1007,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the island of Hispaniola (Haiti and the Dominican Republic), growing in a wide variety of forest types from dry thorn forest to cloud forest, from 300-1900 m.
</paragraph>
