<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[835,1436,503,963]" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
I have located no duplicates of the five specimens were cited by Urban in describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. E. Schulz" authorityYear="1909" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="polyacanthos" variety="oreophilum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Solanum polyacanthos</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[934,1218,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">oreophilum – Nectoux s.n</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
., 
<emphasis box="[1238,1367,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Picarda 245</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Buch 915</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[934,1040,803,829]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Buch 949</emphasis>
, all from Haiti. A photograph of a duplicate of 
<emphasis box="[976,1080,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Buch 949</emphasis>
at IJ is held at MO and is clearly 
<taxonomicName box="[863,1033,870,896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polyacanthos">
<emphasis box="[863,1033,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. polyacanthos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have not lectotypified this name here in the hopes of eventually finding and personally examining duplicates of the syntype material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
